{"profile":{"awsPrograms":[{"category":"Container Hero","joinedAt":2018.0,"memberStatus":"ACTIVE","programName":"HERO"}],"basicInfo":{"alias":"mumoshu","avatar":"https://avatars.builderprofile.aws.dev/2xnIaiptlllqyC8tIkTMKEvu1Pe.webp","bio":"Yusuke has been an AWS Container Hero since 2018, when he was working for freee K.K., a Japanese fintech company that provides a comprehensive web-based ERP suite.\n\nHe introduced both self-hosted Kubernetes on AWS and an EKS-based internal platform that serves many production workloads across several companies.\n\nHe also contributed to and continues to maintain various open-source projects related to Kubernetes and AWS, including actions-runner-controller (now part of GitHub), Helmfile (still widely used), and others.\n\nHe is now part of SurrealDB, which builds a scalable and embeddable multi-model database, envisioning a database that is as general as it applies to many real-world workloads, like containers have been.","builderProfileId":"36f0a519-14ea-48f6-97cb-3690a96b4d86","createdOn":1.7338793984E12,"isStaff":false,"name":"Yusuke Kuoka"},"location":{},"profileStatus":"ACTIVE","socials":{"blog":"","devto":"","github":"mumoshu","linkedIn":"ykuoka","twitter":"mumoshu","youtube":""}}}